<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head><%- include('partials/head') %></head>
<body>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:2rem;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">Company profile</div>
    <h1>ZeroDay Security Services</h1>
    <p class="lead">A cybersecurity research and development practice spanning offensive security tooling, applied research, and hands-on security education. <strong>ZeroDay Academy</strong> is our training platform, built to teach vulnerabilities the way we actually find them.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="container">
  <div class="challenge-grid">
    <div class="glass panel">
      <h3 style="color:var(--cyan);">Development</h3>
      <p>Custom security platforms and tooling — from continuous threat exposure management to investigation platforms built for real operational use.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="glass panel">
      <h3 style="color:var(--fuchsia);">Research</h3>
      <p>Vulnerability research and threat intelligence work that feeds directly back into the labs, challenges, and content we publish here.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="glass panel">
      <h3 style="color:var(--amber);">Education</h3>
      <p>CTF design, training content, and platforms like ZeroDay Academy — built to teach the mechanics of vulnerabilities, not just their names.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="glass panel">
    <h2>Why ZeroDay Academy exists</h2>
    <p>Reading about a vulnerability class and exploiting one yourself are different skills. Every lab here runs real, deliberately vulnerable code — not a quiz — so the exploitation, the fix, and the underlying flaw all stay connected to something you actually did, not just something you read.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
